      ["Treat Tossing", "Yes (~15 treats)", "Yes (~20 treats)"],
      ["Smart Assistant", "Works with Alexa", "Alexa Built-In"],
      ["Bark Alerts", "Yes (dog-specific AI)", "Yes (general)"],
      ["Night Vision", "1080p IR", "1080p IR"],
      ["Subscription", "$5.99/mo (Furbo Nanny)", "$5.99/mo (Petcube Care)"],
      ["Warranty", "1 year", "1 year"],
    ],
    faqs: [
      { q: "Which camera has better treat tossing?", a: "Both work well with small, round treats. The Petcube holds slightly more treats (~20 vs ~15), but the Furbo's tossing is slightly more reliable. Neither is a decisive winner on treats alone." },
      { q: "Is built-in Alexa in the Petcube really useful?", a: "If you already use Alexa for smart home control, yes — the Bites 2 replaces a separate Echo Dot. You can ask it to play music, set timers, control lights, and more, all while serving as your pet camera. If you're not an Alexa user, this feature adds cost without benefit." },
      { q: "Which has better video quality — Furbo or Petcube?", a: "Both are 1080p with solid night vision. The Furbo's 360° pan/tilt gives you more viewing flexibility. The Petcube's 160° wide angle covers more area at once but you can't move it. For active pets that roam, Furbo wins. For pets that stay in one spot, Petcube's wide angle is cleaner." },
    ],
  },
  "litter-robot-4-vs-petsafe-scoopfree": {
    title: "Litter-Robot 4 vs PetSafe ScoopFree (2026) — Sifting vs Crystal, Which Wins?",
    description: "Litter-Robot 4 vs PetSafe ScoopFree head-to-head. We compare sifting vs crystal litter systems, cost over time, odor control, and which self-cleaning box is right for your cat.",
    winner: "The Litter-Robot 4 wins on long-term value and cat comfort despite a higher upfront cost. Over 3 years, the ScoopFree's proprietary crystal tray costs ($15-25/month) add up to $540-900 — nearly matching the LR4's $699 price. The LR4's sifting system works with any clumping litter, gives you more flexibility, and most cats prefer traditional litter texture. Get the ScoopFree only if you specifically want crystal litter's low-dust benefits or need the lowest entry price.",
    productAId: "litter-robot-4",
    productBId: "petsafe-scoopfree",
    comparisonRows: [
      ["Price", "$699", "$299"],
      ["Rating", "★★★★½ (4.5)", "★★★★⅕ (4.2)"],
      ["Litter Type", "Any clumping litter", "Crystal litter only"],
      ["3-Year Total Cost", "$699 + $200 supplies = ~$900", "$299 + $540-900 trays = ~$840-1,200"],
      ["Odor Control", "Carbon filter + sealed drawer", "Crystal absorption + disposable tray"],
      ["Multi-Cat", "Up to 4 cats", "Best for 1-2 cats"],
      ["Cleaning Mechanism", "Rotating sifting globe", "Rake with disposable tray"],
      ["Warranty", "1 year", "1 year"],
    ],
    faqs: [
      { q: "Which is cheaper over time — Litter-Robot 4 or PetSafe ScoopFree?", a: "Surprisingly, the $699 Litter-Robot 4 can be cheaper over 3 years. The LR4 uses regular clumping litter (~$10-15/month), while ScoopFree requires proprietary crystal trays at $15-25 each lasting 2-4 weeks ($20-40/month). Over 3 years: LR4 ~$900-1,200 total, ScoopFree ~$840-1,500 total depending on tray usage." },
      { q: "Is crystal litter better than clumping litter?", a: "Crystal litter excels at odor absorption and produces less dust — great for cats with respiratory issues. However, some cats dislike the texture and refuse to use it. Clumping litter feels more natural to cats and the LR4's sifting system handles it perfectly. If your cat is picky, the LR4 is the safer choice." },
      { q: "Which is easier to maintain — LR4 or ScoopFree?", a: "The ScoopFree wins on simplicity — just swap the disposable tray every 2-4 weeks. No scooping, no cleaning the globe. The LR4 requires emptying the waste drawer weekly and occasional deep cleaning of the globe. For 'set it and forget it' convenience, ScoopFree is easier. For long-term cost and flexibility, LR4 is better." },
