      { q: "Is the YEAPAW really worth $54 more?", a: "It depends on your priorities. The YEAPAW's pumpless design means zero motor noise and zero pump maintenance — there's literally no pump to fail. Its 100% stainless steel construction (including the bowl interior) means no water ever touches plastic. For hygiene purists and ultra-quiet homes, yes. For most cats who just want running water, the Pioneer Pet does the job beautifully at $39." },
      { q: "Which fountain is quieter?", a: "The YEAPAW is virtually silent because it has no mechanical pump — water circulates via an electromagnetic field. The Pioneer Pet uses a traditional submersible pump which is very quiet (most owners report hearing only gentle water trickling), but you may notice a faint hum in a completely silent room. If the fountain sits in a bedroom, YEAPAW wins." },
      { q: "Which is easier to clean?", a: "Both are dishwasher safe, but the Pioneer Pet has fewer parts to disassemble. The YEAPAW's pumpless base is clever but has more nooks to clean thoroughly. Pioneer Pet's simpler design means faster cleaning — about 5 minutes vs 8-10 for YEAPAW. Neither is difficult, but Pioneer Pet wins on simplicity." },
      { q: "Do cats prefer one over the other?", a: "Both use stainless steel surfaces that cats instinctively prefer over plastic. Most cats will drink from either happily. The Pioneer Pet's raindrop shape creates a gentler water flow that timid cats may prefer. The YEAPAW's design produces a more visible water stream that curious cats find engaging. If you have a skittish cat, Pioneer Pet's subtler flow is the safer bet." },
    ],
